    "recap_headline": "Rice University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "Phoenix, AZ-\nGaret Boehm's\none-out single in the bottom of the ninth capped a furious late rally by Rice and gave the Owls a 6-5 win over Saint Mary's in Phoenix, Arizona, on Friday afternoon.\nHow it Happened:\nFirst-time starter\nTanner Wiggins\nheld the potent Gaels offense off the scoreboard despite seven hits in the first four innings but gave up solo runs in the fifth and sixth. At the same time, SMC starter John Damozonio held Rice hitless until Hiram Bocachica's two-out double in the bottom of the fifth. The Owls finally solved Damozonio in the sixth, packaging three straight hits to tie the game 2-2 on\nMason Ashlock's\ntwo-run double.\u00a0 Saint Mary's exploded for three runs in the top of the eighth but Rice had an immediate answer in its half of the inning.\nPaul Smith\nled off with a walk, and Boehm followed with a single. One out later,\nKutter-Gage Webb\nbrought in Smith with a single, and Boehm scored, and Webb moved to third on a sacrifice fly by\nLorenzo Rios\n. Freshman\nMasa Chilcutt\ntied the game with a single on a 3-1 pitch.\nJax Traeger\nset the stage for a walkoff in the ninth by retiring SMC in order for the first time in the game. Pinch hitter\nLandon West\nopened with a walk and was replaced by Daigre who moved to second on a sac bunt by\nCole Green\n.\u00a0 Smith was intentionally walked to set up a double play, but Boehm wasted no time for any further drama, lining the first pitch he saw into left center for the game-winner.\nNext Up:\nRice will be back in action Brazell Field at 8 p.m., facing \u00a0Grand Canyon.\nNotes\nRice improved to 10-8 on the season, 4-5 on the road, and 5-1 on Fridays, 4-1 in series openers, and 4-1 at Brazell Field.\nRice reached double figures in 18 games, the earliest in a season it has done so since the Owls were 10-8 in 2021.\nWiggins worked 6.1 innings in his first career start, the longest by an Owl this year in a series-opener.\nAshlock has hit in six of his last seven (.300, 6x20)."
  },
